# Stage — local network secrets (TEMPLATE)

> Copy this file to `ops/network.local.md` and fill in your venue's real
> values. The real file is **gitignored** so credentials and concrete addresses
> never reach the public repo; this `.example` is committed as the onboarding
> guide. The reusable *architecture* and recipe live in the public `CLAUDE.md`
> "Network setup" section — read that first; this file is only the per-venue
> blanks to fill in.
>
>     cp ops/network.local.md.example ops/network.local.md
>     # then edit ops/network.local.md with your real values

## Pi access

- Pi hostname: `raspberrypi`
- Pi Tailscale IP: `100.x.y.z`            # from `tailscale ip -4` on the Pi
- Admin/dev access: `ssh <user>@100.x.y.z`
- Admin page: `http://100.x.y.z:3000/admin` (from any device on your tailnet)
- Public Caddy proxy target: `100.x.y.z:3000`

## Guest WiFi (OpenWrt AP on the router, e.g. Linksys WRT1900ACS)

- SSID: `<your-guest-ssid>`
- Password: `<your-guest-wifi-password>`

## Upstream room WiFi (the venue's internet, used by the Pi + OpenWrt wwan)

- SSID: `<venue-wifi-ssid>`
- Password: `<venue-wifi-password>`

## Verified addresses (record yours once, dated, from the Pi over Tailscale)

- Pi Tailscale IP: `100.x.y.z`
- Pi room-WiFi IP: `<a.b.c.d/nn>` on `wlan0`        # `ip -4 addr show wlan0`
- Pi guest-LAN IP: `192.168.1.NNN/24` on `eth0`     # static OpenWrt DHCP lease
- OpenWrt LAN config: `network.lan.ipaddr='192.168.1.1/24'`
- OpenWrt DHCP: start `100`, limit `150`, lease time `12h`
- OpenWrt `wwan`: `<a.b.c.d/nn>` via room WiFi, gateway/DNS `<router-ip>`

## Observed guest-network DHCP behavior (a laptop joined to the guest AP)

- Client IP example: `192.168.1.NNN`
- Guest subnet: `192.168.1.0/24`
- Router/DHCP server: `192.168.1.1`
- DNS handed out by DHCP: `192.168.1.1`
- DHCP search domain: `lan`
- Pi guest-network IP: `192.168.1.NNN` via static OpenWrt DHCP lease
- Pi DHCP hostname resolves as `raspberrypi.lan` via OpenWrt dnsmasq
- `dreamfinder.lan` resolves to the Pi's guest-LAN IP via OpenWrt dnsmasq

---

## Server config (systemd drop-in, NOT this file)

Network secrets live here; the Stage *server*'s environment variables live in a
private systemd drop-in so they're injected into `stage-server.service` without
being committed. Create one with:

    systemctl --user edit stage-server.service

and add (only the ones you need):

    [Service]
    # Public join URL the QR code points at. Defaults to
    # https://imagineering.cc/stage; override per venue.
    Environment=STAGE_JOIN_URL=https://your-domain.example/stage

    # Optional: Dreamfinder-authored facilitation questions via the OpenAI
    # Responses API. WITHOUT a model key the room labels analysis as
    # source-backed facilitation rather than generated commentary.
    Environment=STAGE_OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...
    Environment=STAGE_OPENAI_MODEL=gpt-5.4-mini

    # Optional: raise the GitHub API rate limit for evidence search over
    # consenting participants' public repos. A read-only/no-scope token is fine.
    Environment=STAGE_GITHUB_TOKEN=ghp_...

Operational toggles also read from the environment (see `server.js`):

    # STAGE_NO_AUDIO=1     run without mpv (CI / a Pi with no audio sink)
    # STAGE_STATE_FILE=... override the persisted-state path (default stage-state.json)
